step_description_1: UE in 5GMM-DEREGISTERED state sends REGISTRATION REQUEST message to AMF
step_description_2: UE in 5GMM-DEREGISTERED state sends a REGISTRATION REQUEST message to the AMF to initiate initial registration.

step_description_1: UE handles the 5GS mobile identity IE in the following order
step_description_2: AMF may initiate 5GMM common procedures, such as identification, authentication, and security mode control, based on the information in the REGISTRATION REQUEST.

step_description_1: If SUCI is included and T3519 is not running, start T3519 and store SUCI value
step_description_2: If the initial registration request is accepted, the AMF sends a REGISTRATION ACCEPT message to the UE. It assigns a TAI list to the UE.

step_description_1: Include UE status IE if operating in dual-registration mode and in EMM-REGISTERED state
step_description_2: Upon receipt of the REGISTRATION ACCEPT message, the UE enters the 5GMM-REGISTERED state and sets the 5GS update status to 5U1 UPDATED.

step_description_1: Include last visited registered TAI if available
step_description_2: The UE sends a REGISTRATION COMPLETE message to the AMF to acknowledge the successful update of the network slicing information, if certain conditions are met.

step_description_1: Include 5GS update type IE if SMS over NAS is requested, otherwise include 5GS update type IE
step_description_2: AMF stops timer T3550, set itself to 5GMM-REGISTERED after receiving REGISTRATION COMPLETE
